  "body": "Hi guys,\r\n\r\nYou can run blew code:\r\n\r\n```\r\nfunc TestEncodeDecodeStructPoint(t *testing.T) {\r\n\ttype A struct {\r\n\t\tA1 string\r\n\t}\r\n\ttype B struct {\r\n\t\tAPoint *A\r\n\t\tB1     string\r\n\t}\r\n\tb := &B{APoint: nil, B1: \"b\"}\r\n\tby, err := EncodeToBytes(b)\r\n\tif err != nil {\r\n\t\tt.Log(err.Error())\r\n\t}\r\n\tt.Logf(\"B:[%x]\", by)  //print: B:[c2c062]\r\n\tb2 := &B{}\r\n\terr = DecodeBytes(by, b2)\r\n\tif err != nil {\r\n\t\tt.Log(err.Error())  //Error: rlp: too few elements for rlp.A, decoding into (rlp.B).APoint\r\n\t}\r\n}\r\n```\r\nrlp.DecodeBytes will throw exception  **too few elements for rlp.A, decoding into (rlp.B).APoint**",
